 three different ways.', 'The prime factorisation of 36 is $2 \times 2 \times 3 \times 3$. The factor trees demonstrate different paths to reach this prime factorisation.', null, null, 'A factor tree is a diagram used to break down a number into its prime factors. The number 36 can be factorised in several ways. For example, 36 can be split into $2 \times 18$, $3 \times 12$, or $4 \times 9$. Each branch is then further broken down until all numbers at the end of the branches are prime numbers. In all cases, the prime factorisation of 36 will be $2 \times 2 \times 3 \times 3$.', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 'short_answer', 'medium', 'true', 'false', 'true', 'true', null, null, '[SVG(svg=''<svg> <g> <circle cx="100" cy="20" r="15" stroke="black" stroke-width="1" fill="white" /> <text x="100" y="25" text-anchor="middle">36</text> </g> <g> <line x1="70" y1="40" x2="30" y2="60" stroke="black" stroke-width="1" /> <line x1="130" y1="40" x2="170" y2="60" stroke="black" stroke-width="1" /> <circle cx="30" cy="70" r="15" stroke="black" stroke-width="1" fill="white" /> <text x="30" y="75" text-anchor="middle">2</text> <circle cx="170" cy="70" r="15" stroke="black" stroke-width="1" fill="white" /> <text x="170" y="75" text-anchor="middle">18</text> </g> <g> <line x1="170" y1="90" x2="130" y2="110" stroke="black" stroke-width="1" /> <line x1="170" y1="90" x2="210" y2="110" stroke="black" stroke-width="1" /> <circle cx="130" cy="120" r="15" stroke="black" stroke-width="1" fill="white" /> <text x="130" y="125" text-anchor="middle">2</text> <circle cx="210" cy="120" r="15" stroke="black" stroke-width="1" fill="white" /> <text x="210" y="125" text-anchor="middle">9</text> </g> <g> <line x1="210" y1="140" x2="170" y2="160" stroke="black" stroke-width="1" /> <line x1="210" y1="140" x2="250" y2="160" stroke="black" stroke-width="1" /> <circle cx="170" cy="170" r="15" stroke="black" stroke-width="1" fill="white" /> <text x="170" y="175" text-anchor="middle">3</t