s 3$. The common prime factors appearing in all three factorisations are two 2s. So, HCF(20, 28, 36) = $2 \times 2 = 4$. Therefore, the greatest denomination of stamps she must buy is 4.', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 'short_answer', 'medium', 'true', 'false', 'false', 'false', null, null, null), ('0270a0bb-d732-51da-9181-b9befb1b496d', '2026-02-04 12:28:31.310287+00', '2026-02-04 12:28:31.310287+00', '11ea3956-d46e-4476-bb2c-a50afa027f5c', null, 'Bisect the given angle PQR.', 'QA bisects $\angle$PQR', null, null, 'Steps of construction:Step 1: With Q as centre and any convenient radius, draw an arc intersecting arms QP and QR of $\angle$PQR at M and N respectively.Step 2: With N and M as centres and radius more than half of MN, draw two arcs (in the interior of $\angle$Q) intersecting at A.Step 3: Join QA and extend it to get a ray QA.Thus, QA bisects $\angle$PQR. We can verify by measuring $\angle$AQP and $\angle$AQR using a protractor.', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 'short_answer', null, 'true', 'false', 'true', 'true', null, null, null), ('02d89ad9-95b8-53b9-9204-69f7580f4be5', '2026-02-04 12:31:36.914575+00', '2026-02-04 12:31:36.914575+00', '11ea3956-d46e-4476-bb2c-a50afa027f5c', null, 'Find the smallest number which when reduced by 6 is divisible by 12, 15, 20 and 27.', 'The smallest number divisible by 12, 15, 20, and 27 is their LCM. LCM of 12, 15, 20, and 27 is $2 \times 2 \times 3 \times 3 \times 3 \times 5 = 540$. The smallest number which when reduced by 6 is divisible by 12, 15, 20, and 27 is (LCM of 12, 15, 20, and 27) + 6. Thus, the required number = $(540 + 6) = 546$.', null, null, 'If a number, when reduced by 6, is divisible by 12, 15, 20, and 27, it means that (number - 6) is a common multiple of these numbers. We need the smallest such number, so (number - 6) must be the LCM of 12, 15, 20, and 27. Using common division for LCM(12, 15, 20, 27): Divide by 2: (6, 15, 10, 27). Divide by 2: (3, 15, 5, 27). Divide by 3: (1, 5, 5, 9). Divide by 3: (1, 5, 5, 3). Divide by 3: (1, 5, 5, 1). Divide by 5: (1, 1, 1, 1). LCM = $2 \times 2 \times 3 \times 3 \times 3 \times 5 = 540$. The required number is $540 + 6 = 546$.', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 'short_answer', 'medium', 'true', 'false', 'false', 'false', null, null, null), ('0303175a-8f3a-5825-b812-7eb53ca93a1b', '2026-02-04 12:31:36.914575+00', '2026-02-04 12:31:36.914575+00', '11ea3956-d46e-4476-bb2c-a50afa027f5c', null, 'Find the LCM of 108, 135 and 162 by common division method.', 'Using common division method:
2 | 108, 135, 162
2 | 54, 135, 81
3 | 27, 135, 81
3 | 9, 45, 27
3 | 3, 15, 9
3 | 1, 5, 3
5 | 1, 5, 1
  | 1, 1, 1
LCM of 108, 135 and 162 is $2 \times 2 \times 3 \times 3 \times 3 \times 3 \times 5 = 1620$.', null, null, 'To find the LCM of 108, 135, and 162 using the common division method: Divide by 2: (54, 135, 81). Divide by 2: (27, 135, 81). Divide by 3: (9, 45, 27). Divide by 3: (3, 15, 9). Divide by 3: (1, 5, 3). Divide by 3: (1, 5, 1). Divide by 5: (1, 1, 1). Multiply all the divisors: $2 \times 2 \times 3 \times 3 \times 3 \times 3 \times 5 = 1620$. So, LCM(108, 135, 162) = 1620.', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 'short_answer', 'medium', 'true', 'false', 'false', 'false', null, null, null), ('030abf82-049f-50c9-bc0d-15054e154593', '2026-02-04 12:28:31.310287+00', '2026-02-04 12:28:31.310287+00', '11ea3956-d46e-4476-bb2c-a50afa027f5c', null, 'Construct an angle of measure 60$^{\circ}$ using a ruler and compasses.', '$\angle$NAB = 60$^{\circ}$', null, null, 'Steps given below:Step 1: Draw a ray AB.Step 2: With A as centre and any convenient radius, draw an arc cutting ray AB at M.Step 3: With M as centre and same radius, draw an arc intersecting previous arc at N.Step 4: Join AN and extend it to get a ray.Thus, $\angle$NAB is the required angle of measure 60$^{\circ}$.', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 'short_answer', null, 'true', 'false', 'true', 'true', null, null, null), ('0aceaccc-d6d7-50f8-bf05-fa8f447a0b7f', '2026-02-04 12:31:36.914575+00', '2026-02-04 12:31:36.914575+00', '11ea3956-d46e-4476-bb2c-a50afa027f5c', null, 'Express 980 as the product of primes.', 'Using the division method: $980 \div 2 = 490$, $490 \div 2 = 245$, $245 \div 5 = 49$, $49 \div 7 = 7$, $7 \div 7 = 1$. Hence, $980 = 2 \times 2 \times 5 \times 7 \times 7$.', null, null, 'To express 980 as a product of primes using the division method, we repeatedly divide 980 by the smallest prime numbers until the quotient is 1. Start with 2: $980 \div 2 = 490$. $490 \div 2 = 245$. Now 245 is not divisible by 2 or 3. It ends in 5, so it''s divisible by 5: $245 \div 5 = 49$. 49 is divisible by 7: $49 \div 7 = 7$. $7 \div 7 = 1$. Combining these, $980 = 2 \times 2 \times 5 \times 7 \times 7$.', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 'short_answer', 'medium', 'true', 'false', 'false', 'false', null, null, null), ('0adb44b0-9f46-5eb3-90ce-77aee1f7e407', '2026-02-04 12:28:31.602791+00', '2026-02-04 12:28:31.602791+00', '11ea3956-d46e-4476-bb2c-a50afa027f5c', null, 'Write opposites of the following : (i) $40 \text{ km north}$ (ii) $325 \text{ BCE}$ (iii) $\text{loss of } \text{\textdollar}500$ (iv) $115 \text{ m above sea level}$ (v) $\text{decrease in weight}$', 'Opposite of $40 \text{ km north}$ is $40 \text{ km south}$. Opposite of $325 \text{ BCE}$ is $325 \text{ CE}$. Opposite of $\text{loss of } \text{\textdollar}500$ is $\text{gain of } \text{\textdollar}500$. Opposite of $115 \text{ m above sea level}$ is $115 \text{ m below sea level}$. Opposite of $\text{decrease in weight}$ is $\text{increase in weight}$.', null, null, '(i) $40 \text{ km south}$ (ii) $325 \text{ CE}$ (iii) $\text{gain of } \text{\textdollar}500$ (iv) $115 \text{ m below sea level}$ (v) $\text{increase in weight}$', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 'short_answer', null, 'true', 'false', 'false', 'false', null, null, null), ('0cfd436e-6b71-5a42-9823-8b1ab596ceef', '2026-02-04 12:28:31.486038+00', '2026-02-04 12:28:31.486038+00', '11ea3956-d46e-4476-bb2c-a50afa027f5c', null, 'Check whether the fractions are equivalent :(i) $\frac{2}{3}$ and $\frac{10}{15}$(ii) $\frac{11}{18}$ and $\frac{6}{9}$', '(i) For $\frac{2}{3}$ and $\frac{10}{15}$: Cross products are $2 \times 15 = 30$ and $3 \times 10 = 30$. Since the cross products are equal ($30 = 30$), the fractions are equivalent.(ii) For $\frac{11}{18}$ and $\frac{6}{9}$: Cross products are $11 \times 9 = 99$ and $18 \times 6 = 108$. Since the cross products are not equal ($99 \ne 108$), the fractions are not equivalent.', null, null, 'To check if two fractions $\frac{a}{b}$ and $\frac{c}{d}$ are equivalent, we perform cross-multiplication. If $a \times d = b \times c$, then the fractions are equivalent.', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 'short_answer', 'medium', 'true', 'false', 'false', 'false', null, null, null), ('0e7d3f7d-ee43-540d-8803-859eaedf485f', '2026-02-04 12:28:31.773321+00', '2026-02-04 12:28:31.773321+00', '11ea3956-d46e-4476-bb2c-a50afa027f5c', null, 'Two sides of a triangle are $12$ cm and $14$ cm. The perimeter of the triangle is $36$ cm. What is the length of its third side?', '$10$ cm', null, null, 'Let $a, b, c$ be three sides of the triangle, where $a = 12$ cm, $b = 14$ cm. Perimeter of triangle = $a + b + c$. $36 = 12 + 14 + c \Rightarrow 36 = 26 + c \Rightarrow c = 36 - 26 = 10$ cm. Thus, the length of third side of the triangle is $10$ cm.', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 'short_answer', null, 'true', 'false', 'false', 'false', null, null, null), ('103a368a-acd0-5cd8-9287-1d2025ee92e4', '2026-02-04 12:31:36.914575+00', '2026-02-04 12:31:36.914575+00', '11ea3956-d46e-4476-bb2c-a50afa027f5c', null, 'Find the HCF of 1045 and 1520 using long division method.', 'The numbers are 1045 and 1520. $1520 \div 1045$, remainder 475. $1045 \div 475$, remainder 95. $475 \div 95$, remainder 0. Thus, the HCF of 1045 and 1520 is 95.', null, null, 'To find the HCF of 1045 and 1520 using the long division method: Divide 1520 by 1045. $1520 = 1045 \times 1 + 475$. Divide 1045 by 475. $1045 = 475 \times 2 + 95$. Divide 475 by 95. $475 = 95 \times 5 + 0$. The last divisor is 95. Thus, HCF(1045, 1520) = 95.', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 'short_answer', 'medium', 'true', 'false', 'false', 'false', null, null, null), ('116f89cb-4e1a-5ba0-9fdc-a2da584395be', '2026-02-04 12:28:31.967896+00', '2026-02-04 12:28:31.967896+00', '11ea3956-d46e-4476-bb2c-a50afa027f5c', null, 'Write each of the following in figures: (i) One hundred fifty-six point three two six(ii) Zero point one eight seven(iii) Six and seven-hundredths(iv) Five and nine-thousandths(v) One hundred forty-six and seven-hundredths', '(i) $156.326$(ii) $0.187$(iii) $6.07$(iv) $5.009$(v) $146.07$', null, null, 'Here are the decimal representations for each: (i) One hundred fifty-six point three two six $= 156.326$(ii) Zero point one eight seven $= 0.187$(iii) Six and seven-hundredths $= 6 + \frac{7}{100} = 6.07$(iv) Five and nine-thousandths $= 5 + \frac{9}{1000} = 5.009$(v) One hundred forty-six and seven-hundredths $= 146 + \frac{7}{100} = 146.07$', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 'short_answer', 'easy', 'true', 'false', 'false', 'false', null, null, null), ('120e5362-e785-5ef7-bbd7-b6ac90d9039b', '2026-02-04 12:31:33.29782+00', '2026-02-04 12:31:33.29782+00', '11ea3956-d46e-4476-bb2c-a50afa027f5c', null, 'Divide ₹75 in the ratio $2:3$ between Ravi and Rajan.', 'Ravi gets ₹30 and Rajan gets ₹45.', null, null, 'SOLUTION: Sum of the terms of the ratio = $2 + 3 = 5$. Ravi''s share = $\frac{2}{5} \times ₹75 = ₹30$. Rajan''s share = $\frac{3}{5} \times ₹75 = ₹45$.', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 'short_answer', null, 'true', 'false', 'false', 'false', null, null, null), ('1426e315-a824-58c1-9aee-11ea637f755e', '2026-02-04 12:28:31.967896+00', '2026-02-04 12:28:31.967896+00', '11ea3956-d46e-4476-bb2c-a50afa027f5c', null, 'Between which two whole numbers on the number line do the following numbers lie? Which of these whole numbers is nearer the number? (i) $0.3$(ii) $6.7$(iii) $4.4$', '', null, null, '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 'short_answer', null, 'true', 'false', 'false', 'true', null, null, '[SVG(svg=''$\\\\begin{array}{rcccccccccc}\\\\{}\\\\;\\\\text{0}\\\\\\\\;\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\