ectangular sheet is $9:5$. If the width of the sheet is 15 cm, find its length.', 'The length of the rectangular sheet is 27 cm.', null, null, 'SOLUTION: Let the length of the rectangular sheet be $x$ cm. The ratio of length to width is $9:5$. The second ratio of length to width is $x:15$. Therefore, $9:5::x:15$. Using the property that product of extremes = product of means, we have $9 \times 15 = 5 \times x$. $135 = 5x$. $x = \frac{135}{5} = 27$. Thus, the length of the rectangular sheet is 27 cm.', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 'short_answer', null, 'true', 'false', 'false', 'false', null, null, null), ('1ba9b6f5-5aef-5572-a029-de5d8c90d159', '2026-02-04 12:31:36.914575+00', '2026-02-04 12:31:36.914575+00', '11ea3956-d46e-4476-bb2c-a50afa027f5c', null, 'The HCF of two numbers is 12 and their product is 2160. Find their LCM.', 'Product of two numbers = HCF $\times$ LCM. $2160 = 12 \times \text{LCM}$. $\text{LCM} = 2160 \div 12 = 180$. Thus, the LCM of two numbers is 180.', null, null, 'We use the relationship formula: Product of two numbers = HCF $\times$ LCM. Given product = 2160 and HCF = 12. So, $2160 = 12 \times \text{LCM}$. To find LCM, divide 2160 by 12. LCM = $2160 \div 12 = 180$.', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 'short_answer', 'medium', 'true', 'false', 'false', 'false', null, null, null), ('1c3daed0-4c61-59a4-a021-bd6877acf615', '2026-02-04 12:28:31.967896+00', '2026-02-04 12:28:31.967896+00', '11ea3956-d46e-4476-bb2c-a50afa027f5c', null, 'What should be subtracted from $9.89$ to get $0.761$?', '$9.129$', null, null, 'Let the number to be subtracted be $x$.
