wo arcs intersecting at C.Step 6: Join OC and extend it to get a ray OC.Thus, $\angle$COA is the required angle of measure 90$^{\circ}$.', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 'short_answer', null, 'true', 'false', 'true', 'true', null, null, null), ('505fef11-05a1-5358-9aae-79770fbaf256', '2026-02-04 12:28:31.311736+00', '2026-02-04 12:28:31.311736+00', '11ea3956-d46e-4476-bb2c-a50afa027f5c', null, 'Copy the following drawing (an incomplete L-shape on a grid with two dotted lines) on squared paper. Complete the figure such that the resulting figure has two dotted lines as two lines of symmetry.', 'The figure is completed by drawing the missing parts using both lines of symmetry.', null, null, 'These figures can be completed by drawing similar parts as shown in the completed figures (Page 9), first about the vertical line of symmetry and then about the horizontal line of symmetry, or vice-versa. This creates a figure with two lines of symmetry.', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 'short_answer', 'medium', 'true', 'false', 'true', 'true', null, null, null), ('51402988-1b9d-5e37-84b1-d5d16e6d06ff', '2026-02-04 12:28:31.486038+00', '2026-02-04 12:28:31.486038+00', '11ea3956-d46e-4476-bb2c-a50afa027f5c', null, 'Write four equivalent fractions of $\frac{2}{5}$.', 'Multiplying by 2, 3, 4, and 5 respectively:$\frac{2 \times 2}{5 \times 2} = \frac{4}{10}$$\frac{2 \times 3}{5 \times 3} = \frac{6}{15}$$\frac{2 \times 4}{5 \times 4} = \frac{8}{20}$$\frac{2 \times 5}{5 \times 5} = \frac{10}{25}$Thus, four equivalent fractions of $\frac{2}{5}$ are $\frac{4}{10}$, $\frac{6}{15}$, $\frac{8}{20}$, and $\frac{10}{25}$.', null, null, 'Equivalent fractions are found by multiplying or dividing both the numerator and denominator by the same non-zero natural number.', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 'short_answer', 'easy', 'true', 'false', 'false', 'false', null, null, null), ('5186a287-b2a2-5108-b14e-c082e4fa5b1c', '2026-02-04 12:28:31.776717+00', '2026-02-04 12:28:31.776717+00', '11ea3956-d46e-4476-bb2c-a50afa027f5c', null, 'Represent $3 + 5$ on the number line.', '$3 + 5 = 8$', null, null, 'Start from 3. Since we have to add 5 to this number, so we make 5 jumps to the right. We get, $3 + 5 = 8$.', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 'short_answer', 'easy', 'true', 'false', 'true', 'true', null, null, null), ('51f8e49d-3fdc-5739-b594-772a52a28016', '2026-02-04 12:31:33.29782+00', '2026-02-04 12:31:33.29782+00', '11ea3956-d46e-4476-bb2c-a50afa027f5c', null, 'The cost of one pen is ₹12. Find the cost of 8 such pens.', 'The cost of 8 pens is ₹96.', null, null, 'SOLUTION: The cost of one pen is given as ₹12. The cost of 8 pens will be eight times the cost of one pen (Unitary Method). Cost of 8 pens = $₹12 \times 8 = ₹96$. Thus, 8 pens cost ₹96.', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 'short_answer', null, 'true', 'false', 'false', 'false', null, null, null), ('528c444c-4c22-5edb-8e35-7471338c9bcf', '2026-02-04 12:31:36.914575+00', '2026-02-04 12:31:36.914575+00', '11ea3956-d46e-4476-bb2c-a50afa027f5c', null, 'Find the LCM of 24, 28 and 196 using common division method.', 'Using common division method:
2 | 24, 28, 196
